  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The earthquake damaged much of Port au Prince&#x2019;s already limited water and sanitation infrastructure, increasing health concerns for residents living in crowded camps. This project aimed to reduce risk of waterborne and vector-borne disease in spontaneous settlements and their peripheries in Port au Prince, and in areas in which transitional shelters were constructed by American Red Cross partners. Services included hygiene promotion and improvements to basic water supply, increased access to safe water and latrines, excreta disposal, drainage, and trash collection</narrative>
  </description>
